content:
Make Smarter Routing Decisions by Checking Agent Availability

Optimize routing by using information collected about your organizationâ€™s capacity to handle new work requests. Add the Check Availability for Routing action to an Omni-Channel flow to determine agent availability and estimated wait time.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

In the Omni-Channel flow, click +, select Check Availability for Routing, give it a label, API name, and description. Select the service channel and specify the queue, agent, or skill to check availability for.

The action can return:

Estimated Wait Time (in seconds) - the estimated time that work can remain in the queue before an agent picks it up.
Number of Online Agents - the number of agents who are online but not necessarily available to accept more work.
Number of Queued Work Items - the number of items waiting to be picked up, excluding items assigned to or accepted by agents.

To make a routing decision based on the results, add a Decision element to the Omni-Channel flow and define the expected routing for different conditions. You can also output the estimated wait time in an Check Availability for Routing action and use that output as input for the routing logic in a Route Work action.
title: Make Smarter Routing Decisions by Checking Agent Availability
